        <div class="seo-stars">★★★★★</div>
        <p>"Turns out our entire service area wasn't ranking because all our service pages had duplicate meta titles. Fixed in a day. Traffic went up 60% in the next 30 days."</p>
        <div class="seo-author"><div class="seo-initials">HS</div><div><strong>Harish Shah</strong><span>Construction Company, Naroda</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 9: FAQ
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="seo-audit-faq reveal">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header centered">
      <span class="section-label">FAQ</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">About the Free SEO Audit</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="seo-faq-grid">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How is this different from a free tool like Semrush or Ubersuggest?</summary>
        <p>Free tools give you raw data, numbers without context. Our audit is a human-reviewed analysis that explains what the numbers mean for your specific business, in your specific market (Ahmedabad / Gujarat), and prioritizes what to fix first. We also include competitor analysis specific to your industry and location.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you need my Google Analytics or Search Console access?</summary>
        <p>If you're willing to share view access to GA4 and Search Console, the audit will be more accurate, especially for traffic data. But it's not required. We can run a thorough audit using third-party tools and public data alone.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is this really free or is there a paid version?</summary>
        <p>The audit report is completely free. We do offer a deeper "SEO Strategy Session" (paid) where we walk through the findings together and build a 6-month roadmap, but the audit itself is always free.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>My website is brand new. Is an SEO audit useful?</summary>
        <p>Very. New sites benefit most because we can identify structural issues before Google has indexed incorrect signals. We'll flag what you need to set up correctly from day one to give yourself the best possible start.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Will the audit show me why a competitor is ranking above me?</summary>
        <p>Yes, if you provide their URL. The competitor gap analysis is one of the most valuable parts of the audit, it shows you specifically what they have (links, content, technical setup) that's giving them the ranking advantage.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How detailed is the report?</summary>
        <p>Typically 10–18 pages covering every component listed above. Each finding is categorised by severity (critical / important / minor), explained in plain language, and given a specific recommendation. No filler, no vague advice.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<CtaBanner
  title="Ready to Find Out Why You're Not Ranking?"
  subtitle="Submit the form above for your free SEO audit, delivered within 48 hours. No sales pressure, just genuine insights."
  ctaLabel="Get My Free SEO Audit →"
  ctaHref="#seo-audit-form"
/>

</PageLayout>

<style>
/* HERO */
.seo-audit-hero {
  padding: 100px 0 clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
  background: linear-gradient(170deg, var(--white) 0%, var(--blue-50) 60%, var(--white) 100%);
}
.seo-audit-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start;
}
.seo-audit-content h1 {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  letter-spacing: -.03em;
  line-height: 1.1;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.seo-audit-content h1 .highlight {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--blue-600), var(--blue-400));
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}
.seo-audit-content > p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--gray-500); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.seo-audit-includes { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.seo-include-item { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start; }
.seo-include-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1; }
.seo-include-item strong { display: block; font-size: .9rem; margin-bottom: .2rem; }
.seo-include-item p { font-size: .85rem; color: var(--gray-500); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
.seo-proof-bar {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  font-size: .85rem;
  color: var(--blue-700);
  font-weight: 600;
  padding-top: 1.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-100);
}

/* FORM CARD */
.seo-audit-form-card {
  background: var(--white);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  padding: 2.5rem;
  border: 1.5px solid var(--blue-100);
  box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(37,99,235,.08);
  position: sticky;
  top: 100px;
  max-width: 480px;
  margin-left: auto;
}
.seo-audit-form-card h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: .4rem; }
